1
00:00:29,620 --> 00:00:32,980
=The Secret of the Lost Pearl=

2
00:00:33,020 --> 00:00:34,940
=Episode 17=
(Fiction. Do not imitate.)

3
00:00:38,520 --> 00:00:40,790
This painting reminds me
of something.

4
00:00:41,670 --> 00:00:44,600
There's an ancient painting
from the Song dynasty.

5
00:00:45,070 --> 00:00:45,960
Have you heard of it?

6
00:00:46,880 --> 00:00:48,350
It's very magical.

7
00:00:49,320 --> 00:00:51,070
This painting can change.

8
00:00:51,790 --> 00:00:52,880
The ox there

9
00:00:53,110 --> 00:00:55,640
is grazing under the tree,

10
00:00:56,320 --> 00:00:57,430
but without light,

11
00:00:57,600 --> 00:00:59,880
it naturally returns to the grass shed

12
00:01:00,110 --> 00:01:01,320
to rest.

13
00:01:03,470 --> 00:01:04,710
Its value lies in the fact

14
00:01:04,870 --> 00:01:06,400
that this painting was treated

15
00:01:06,590 --> 00:01:09,310
with a secret imperial elixir.

16
00:01:09,590 --> 00:01:11,120
So, you're saying

17
00:01:11,640 --> 00:01:14,120
they applied this magical liquid

18
00:01:14,430 --> 00:01:15,590
to the wall in advance.

19
00:01:15,640 --> 00:01:18,230
That's why mercury flowed onto the wall,

20
00:01:18,710 --> 00:01:20,790
creating such beautiful paintings.

21
00:01:21,870 --> 00:01:23,480
The painting is so well done.

22
00:01:24,280 --> 00:01:25,706
Look at the child kicking the ball,

23
00:01:26,280 --> 00:01:27,680
full of spirit.

24
00:01:29,200 --> 00:01:31,510
This ball was called cuju
in the Tang dynasty.

25
00:01:35,790 --> 00:01:36,840
This one is good too,

26
00:01:37,840 --> 00:01:38,870
playing the qin.

27
00:01:40,230 --> 00:01:41,710
So full of artistic charm.

28
00:01:42,920 --> 00:01:44,040
Look at the clothing.

29
00:01:45,350 --> 00:01:46,430
Look at the expressions.

30
00:01:47,710 --> 00:01:49,760
The artistic level is very high.

31
00:01:52,710 --> 00:01:53,550
Lu.

32
00:01:53,790 --> 00:01:54,630
Chubby.

33
00:01:59,200 --> 00:02:00,310
This is the painting we saw

34
00:02:00,310 --> 00:02:01,280
at that old man's place.

35
00:02:03,870 --> 00:02:05,710
Look at the hairstyle and clothing.

36
00:02:06,040 --> 00:02:08,190
The posture and gesture
of the moon-racing figure.

37
00:02:08,430 --> 00:02:09,280
They're the same.

38
00:02:09,680 --> 00:02:10,750
It's that painting.

39
00:02:11,280 --> 00:02:12,960
What painting are you talking about?

40
00:02:12,960 --> 00:02:14,433
The old man of the River King Temple.

41
00:02:14,592 --> 00:02:15,539
We found him worshipping

42
00:02:15,550 --> 00:02:16,760
an ancient painting at home.

43
00:02:16,910 --> 00:02:18,910
It's almost identical to the one we saw.

44
00:02:19,400 --> 00:02:20,310
Look at this painting.

45
00:02:20,560 --> 00:02:23,400
It looks
like a princess marriage painting.

46
00:02:24,520 --> 00:02:25,560
So,

47
00:02:25,710 --> 00:02:27,680
the old man claims
to be the tomb keeper

48
00:02:28,310 --> 00:02:30,560
and has a portrait
of the princess at home.

49
00:02:31,240 --> 00:02:32,750
We can draw a conclusion.

50
00:02:33,080 --> 00:02:34,190
We're at the tomb

51
00:02:34,190 --> 00:02:35,960
of a Tang princess.

52
00:02:37,400 --> 00:02:38,910
If it really is a princess,

53
00:02:39,280 --> 00:02:41,240
judging by the clothing style
in this painting,

54
00:02:41,310 --> 00:02:43,680
she must have married into the Huihu.

55
00:02:43,990 --> 00:02:44,840
Comrades,

56
00:02:44,870 --> 00:02:46,840
I've thought of a big problem.

57
00:02:47,590 --> 00:02:49,560
If this is a princess's tomb,

58
00:02:50,400 --> 00:02:52,520
why is there a man in the coffin?

59
00:02:52,710 --> 00:02:53,550
The prince consort?

60
00:02:56,080 --> 00:02:56,920
Guys,

61
00:02:57,800 --> 00:02:59,400
I also noticed a problem.

62
00:03:02,590 --> 00:03:04,120
This place is bizarre.

63
00:03:04,120 --> 00:03:05,710
Can we go out to study it?

64
00:03:06,150 --> 00:03:07,430
First, find an exit.

65
00:03:07,470 --> 00:03:09,430
Can we discuss it outside?

66
00:03:11,310 --> 00:03:13,800
Lu is right; first, find an exit.

67
00:03:18,680 --> 00:03:19,540
Come on.

68
00:03:19,560 --> 00:03:20,800
One, two, three.

69
00:03:26,960 --> 00:03:28,240
Am I too old?

70
00:03:28,840 --> 00:03:30,750
How come prying

71
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:32,080
exhausts me?

72
00:03:33,960 --> 00:03:34,960
It's not about strength.

73
00:03:35,870 --> 00:03:37,400
It's the oxygen that's lower.

74
00:03:39,280 --> 00:03:40,190
I'm telling you.

75
00:03:40,590 --> 00:03:42,150
I'll be the first to die.

76
00:03:43,710 --> 00:03:46,000
My asthma medicine is all gone.

77
00:03:47,240 --> 00:03:49,590
It's your fault, little girl.

78
00:03:49,630 --> 00:03:51,750
We could've gone back already.

79
00:03:51,960 --> 00:03:52,800
Look at this mess.

80
00:03:52,960 --> 00:03:54,150
Both doors are closed,

81
00:03:54,560 --> 00:03:55,520
trapping us here.

82
00:03:55,910 --> 00:03:56,750
Lu,

83
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:58,360
you can't blame her entirely.

84
00:03:58,710 --> 00:03:59,710
It's also your fault.

85
00:04:00,030 --> 00:04:01,960
What does she have to do with you?

86
00:04:02,150 --> 00:04:04,000
You should've opened the door.

87
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:05,080
Wouldn't that be better?

88
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:07,120
I shouldn't have come.

89
00:04:07,630 --> 00:04:08,630
What was wrong with me?

90
00:04:13,630 --> 00:04:15,190
This door opened a crack.

91
00:04:20,160 --> 00:04:21,000
I know.

92
00:04:21,870 --> 00:04:24,270
It must be related to the music
of the chime bells.

93
00:04:24,800 --> 00:04:25,640
Lu,

94
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:26,840
hit it again.

95
00:04:30,870 --> 00:04:32,000
Why did it close again?

96
00:04:33,830 --> 00:04:34,700
No.

97
00:04:34,750 --> 00:04:36,680
You hit this one first

98
00:04:37,070 --> 00:04:37,920
and then that one.

99
00:04:38,430 --> 00:04:39,360
Let's start over.

100
00:04:48,680 --> 00:04:50,950
Lu, what's the third one?

101
00:04:52,830 --> 00:04:53,830
Just pick any one.

102
00:04:59,630 --> 00:05:00,510
Still not right.

103
00:05:01,630 --> 00:05:02,936
This is like entering a password.

104
00:05:03,510 --> 00:05:05,190
We need to play the melody correctly

105
00:05:05,190 --> 00:05:06,240
for the door to open.

106
00:05:07,160 --> 00:05:08,000
Well.

107
00:05:08,480 --> 00:05:10,720
I'm really impressed with this designer.

108
00:05:10,830 --> 00:05:11,920
Is he reasonable?

109
00:05:12,310 --> 00:05:14,040
To get out, we have to read music?

110
00:05:14,240 --> 00:05:15,870
But we don't know which music.

111
00:05:16,040 --> 00:05:18,310
There are countless scores.

112
00:05:18,430 --> 00:05:19,600
Not to mention lost ones.

113
00:05:19,750 --> 00:05:21,000
What if he composed

114
00:05:21,070 --> 00:05:22,720
an original one?

115
00:05:23,120 --> 00:05:24,160
Don't think too much.

116
00:05:24,360 --> 00:05:25,360
Anyway,

117
00:05:26,270 --> 00:05:27,390
we have to try.

118
00:05:31,630 --> 00:05:32,972
Do you remember the Bagua chambers

119
00:05:32,983 --> 00:05:34,550
I went through with Bai Lingling?

120
00:05:35,120 --> 00:05:36,240
Yes, yes.

121
00:05:36,680 --> 00:05:37,920
Wasn't it just you two alone?

122
00:05:38,430 --> 00:05:39,270
What about it?

123
00:05:39,680 --> 00:05:40,800
Did you two sing inside?

124
00:05:41,510 --> 00:05:42,720
It's the same principle.

125
00:05:42,920 --> 00:05:44,630
The tomb builder set a challenge for us.

126
00:05:44,830 --> 00:05:46,480
Answer correctly, and we can pass.

127
00:05:46,920 --> 00:05:47,920
In the Bagua chambers,

128
00:05:47,920 --> 00:05:48,960
the tomb builder asked me

129
00:05:48,971 --> 00:05:50,390
how I value him.

130
00:05:50,750 --> 00:05:51,776
The chime bell melody here

131
00:05:52,630 --> 00:05:54,510
must also have some meaning.

132
00:05:55,630 --> 00:05:56,800
That makes sense.

133
00:05:57,510 --> 00:05:59,000
But why would a tomb builder

134
00:05:59,480 --> 00:06:01,480
go to such lengths

135
00:06:01,680 --> 00:06:03,680
to test intruders?

136
00:06:03,720 --> 00:06:05,190
We'll know why

137
00:06:05,310 --> 00:06:06,360
when we get out alive.

138
00:06:06,950 --> 00:06:09,800
But what meaning could the melody have?

139
00:06:10,270 --> 00:06:11,680
Let's consider it from two angles.

140
00:06:12,240 --> 00:06:14,160
Who is in the coffin,

141
00:06:14,370 --> 00:06:16,343
and what is their relationship
with the princess?

142
00:06:16,630 --> 00:06:18,950
From the tomb keeper's painting,

143
00:06:18,950 --> 00:06:20,360
the Tang princess in the painting

144
00:06:20,510 --> 00:06:21,800
must be the owner of this tomb.

145
00:06:22,630 --> 00:06:23,920
Combined with the murals,

146
00:06:24,390 --> 00:06:25,310
this princess should be

147
00:06:25,600 --> 00:06:27,680
a princess married into the Huihu.

148
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:28,840
Right?

149
00:06:29,600 --> 00:06:30,440
Right.

150
00:06:31,120 --> 00:06:32,480
Lu, think about it.

151
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:37,160
Which Tang princess married
into the Huihu?

152
00:06:37,270 --> 00:06:38,430
What music would they play

153
00:06:38,680 --> 00:06:40,600
for the marriage?

154
00:06:40,870 --> 00:06:42,160
What music?

155
00:06:43,310 --> 00:06:44,483
I only know that in mid-Tang,

156
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:48,920
there was Princess Ningguo.

157
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:52,920
She married a Huihu khan.

158
00:06:53,240 --> 00:06:54,680
Later, she went to the Huihu.

159
00:06:55,430 --> 00:06:57,720
After the khan died,

160
00:06:57,720 --> 00:06:59,160
she came back to Tang.

161
00:06:59,800 --> 00:07:02,190
As for the music...

162
00:07:05,920 --> 00:07:09,240
After Princess Ningguo returned,

163
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:11,190
did she remarry?

164
00:07:12,120 --> 00:07:14,360
What music was played
at Tang remarriages?

165
00:07:16,510 --> 00:07:17,680
Princess Ningguo

166
00:07:17,680 --> 00:07:19,510
was just a political tool,

167
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:20,440
a pawn.

168
00:07:20,680 --> 00:07:23,000
There are very few historical records.

169
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:24,390
We couldn't have known

170
00:07:24,390 --> 00:07:26,040
the music for her.

171
00:07:27,680 --> 00:07:28,870
The cuju ball

172
00:07:28,920 --> 00:07:30,120
is the only funerary object

173
00:07:30,120 --> 00:07:31,480
we've found in the tomb.

174
00:07:31,920 --> 00:07:33,630
Could there be clues on it?

175
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:39,120
It's just a ball.

176
00:07:39,480 --> 00:07:40,720
What clue could it have?

177
00:07:41,010 --> 00:07:41,870
I know this thing

178
00:07:41,870 --> 00:07:43,160
is from the Tang dynasty.

179
00:07:43,390 --> 00:07:44,843
It was inflated with air

180
00:07:44,854 --> 00:07:46,310
and covered in eight leather panels,

181
00:07:46,310 --> 00:07:47,360
kicked around for fun.

182
00:07:47,830 --> 00:07:49,630
What music could it have?

183
00:07:50,510 --> 00:07:53,240
Would they play music

184
00:07:53,720 --> 00:07:55,160
during a cuju match?

185
00:07:56,600 --> 00:07:58,240
The March of the Athletes?

186
00:08:01,270 --> 00:08:03,310
Anything related to rituals?

187
00:08:03,560 --> 00:08:04,510
Rituals?

188
00:08:05,040 --> 00:08:06,830
I think the person in the coffin

189
00:08:06,830 --> 00:08:08,000
was preserved

190
00:08:08,720 --> 00:08:09,800
because ancient people

191
00:08:10,040 --> 00:08:11,360
mostly believed in rebirth.

192
00:08:12,040 --> 00:08:13,560
That makes sense.

193
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:16,120
Ancient people were very superstitious.

194
00:08:17,070 --> 00:08:18,720
What does that have to do with rituals?

195
00:08:19,510 --> 00:08:20,510
Don't you think

196
00:08:20,720 --> 00:08:22,120
the platform where the coffin is

197
00:08:22,750 --> 00:08:24,750
looks like an altar

198
00:08:24,920 --> 00:08:26,070
when the fire started?

199
00:08:27,830 --> 00:08:29,750
I wouldn't have noticed
if you didn't say it.

200
00:08:29,750 --> 00:08:31,480
But seeing it now,

201
00:08:31,800 --> 00:08:32,910
I think you're right.

202
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:34,120
It's too similar.

203
00:08:34,630 --> 00:08:35,630
Yes, yes.

204
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:38,020
The Music
of the Triumphant Prince of Qin

205
00:08:38,031 --> 00:08:40,120
is related to rituals.

206
00:08:40,360 --> 00:08:42,960
At first, it was for banquets;

207
00:08:42,960 --> 00:08:44,720
later, it was widely used in rituals.

208
00:08:45,030 --> 00:08:46,510
Lu,

209
00:08:46,750 --> 00:08:47,670
hurry up.

210
00:08:47,840 --> 00:08:48,680
Well.

211
00:08:49,440 --> 00:08:50,280
Lu.

212
00:09:02,840 --> 00:09:04,550
Then, I'll do it.

213
00:09:04,550 --> 00:09:05,750
If it causes

214
00:09:05,750 --> 00:09:07,390
any unbearable consequences,

215
00:09:07,390 --> 00:09:09,150
don't blame me.

216
00:09:09,270 --> 00:09:10,110
Hit it.

217
00:09:10,360 --> 00:09:12,360
We have no choice but to try.

218
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:13,440
Fine.

219
00:09:43,750 --> 00:09:44,840
It must be wrong.

220
00:09:45,150 --> 00:09:46,240
Or should I perform

221
00:09:46,240 --> 00:09:48,120
another tune for you?

222
00:09:49,960 --> 00:09:50,820
Play again.

223
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:51,790
Ethnic style?

224
00:09:59,030 --> 00:10:00,720
The air from above

225
00:10:01,550 --> 00:10:03,080
is fresher anyway.

226
00:10:08,200 --> 00:10:09,040
Miss Bai,

227
00:10:09,360 --> 00:10:10,720
the air is getting worse.

228
00:10:11,510 --> 00:10:12,480
I have this.

229
00:10:13,077 --> 00:10:15,110
Do you know quenching thirst
by thinking of plums?

230
00:10:15,870 --> 00:10:16,790
Smell it.

231
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:21,280
This...

232
00:10:22,670 --> 00:10:24,720
Fine, I'll smell it myself.

233
00:10:28,480 --> 00:10:29,550
I'll smell it myself.

234
00:10:34,670 --> 00:10:35,510
You can't sit.

235
00:10:36,200 --> 00:10:37,200
The oxygen is above.

236
00:10:46,910 --> 00:10:48,200
Who's eating chocolate?

237
00:10:53,240 --> 00:10:55,550
Chubby, what are you holding?

238
00:10:55,630 --> 00:10:56,470
It smells so good.

239
00:10:57,320 --> 00:10:58,160
I don't know.

240
00:10:58,320 --> 00:11:00,440
I picked it up when we saved Ms. He.

241
00:11:08,600 --> 00:11:09,510
Let me see it.

242
00:11:19,200 --> 00:11:20,240
It smells so good.

243
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:29,030
It's Wenxiang Jade.

244
00:11:29,270 --> 00:11:32,320
The world has never known
a talking flower,

245
00:11:32,480 --> 00:11:35,670
and now we see jade
giving off fragrance.

246
00:11:37,400 --> 00:11:38,270
Hey, buddy.

247
00:11:38,320 --> 00:11:39,160
I'm telling you.

248
00:11:39,510 --> 00:11:41,720
My asthma medicine is gone.

249
00:11:41,910 --> 00:11:42,870
Smelling this

250
00:11:42,870 --> 00:11:44,910
can ease my asthma.

251
00:11:45,080 --> 00:11:46,320
Please help me out.

252
00:11:46,840 --> 00:11:47,870
- Okay.
- Here.

253
00:11:47,870 --> 00:11:49,136
Take the box; it's the full set.

254
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:53,200
I'm going up first.

255
00:12:00,750 --> 00:12:02,320
Good stuff.

256
00:12:16,630 --> 00:12:17,470
What are you doing?

257
00:12:18,870 --> 00:12:19,840
I'm looking at you.

258
00:12:20,200 --> 00:12:21,040
How are you?

259
00:12:21,360 --> 00:12:22,440
I've been thinking

260
00:12:23,200 --> 00:12:24,510
the tomb owner

261
00:12:24,720 --> 00:12:26,150
must have a very special relationship

262
00:12:26,790 --> 00:12:28,390
with this princess.

263
00:12:29,360 --> 00:12:30,270
What do you mean?

264
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:33,510
Think about it. In a princess's tomb,

265
00:12:33,790 --> 00:12:35,390
a male companion was buried with her,

266
00:12:35,870 --> 00:12:37,150
yet there's nothing

267
00:12:37,230 --> 00:12:38,080
in the tomb

268
00:12:38,080 --> 00:12:39,670
to show his status.

269
00:12:39,990 --> 00:12:40,840
That means he wasn't

270
00:12:40,840 --> 00:12:42,240
a person of high rank.

271
00:12:43,910 --> 00:12:45,000
The only funerary item

272
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:46,320
is that cuju ball.

273
00:12:48,150 --> 00:12:49,320
It's strange.

274
00:12:50,960 --> 00:12:52,030
Could it be that this man

275
00:12:52,550 --> 00:12:54,910
was the princess's cuju coach?

276
00:12:56,270 --> 00:12:57,790
Still joking?

277
00:13:03,150 --> 00:13:04,510
I have a feeling

278
00:13:06,360 --> 00:13:08,030
that, since the Bagua chambers,

279
00:13:08,320 --> 00:13:09,870
the tomb builder

280
00:13:10,200 --> 00:13:11,720
has been sending me a message.

281
00:13:12,790 --> 00:13:14,360
Like a chess game.

282
00:13:15,320 --> 00:13:17,030
He makes a move; I respond.

283
00:13:17,390 --> 00:13:18,870
He makes another; I respond again.

284
00:13:20,480 --> 00:13:22,240
Once I affirmed his self-worth,

285
00:13:22,600 --> 00:13:24,030
he spared me.

286
00:13:25,740 --> 00:13:26,600
We solved

287
00:13:26,600 --> 00:13:28,000
the first mechanism of the coffin;

288
00:13:28,510 --> 00:13:30,120
he allowed us to open it

289
00:13:30,750 --> 00:13:32,150
and see the murals.

290
00:13:34,630 --> 00:13:36,720
Only if we play the melody correctly

291
00:13:37,240 --> 00:13:38,600
will the stone door open.

292
00:13:40,870 --> 00:13:43,000
I can't figure out
what he wants to convey.

293
00:13:44,510 --> 00:13:45,870
I think to him,

294
00:13:46,030 --> 00:13:47,670
I'm just an intruder.

295
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:49,910
Don't be silly.

296
00:13:50,550 --> 00:13:51,840
We can't get out now

297
00:13:52,320 --> 00:13:54,360
because we haven't found
the right music.

298
00:13:55,360 --> 00:13:56,720
It's not your fault.

299
00:13:57,030 --> 00:13:57,870
All these years,

300
00:13:57,870 --> 00:13:58,952
the artifacts you excavated

301
00:13:58,963 --> 00:13:59,960
were perfectly preserved.

302
00:14:00,030 --> 00:14:00,870
I believe

303
00:14:00,870 --> 00:14:02,240
the builder and owner

304
00:14:02,960 --> 00:14:04,030
wouldn't blame you.

305
00:14:04,670 --> 00:14:07,790
Perhaps they might even thank you
in some way.

306
00:14:08,480 --> 00:14:11,270
Is the curse on me
also a form of gratitude?

307
00:14:12,240 --> 00:14:13,200
Who knows?

308
00:14:13,960 --> 00:14:16,200
The future is uncertain.

309
00:14:16,440 --> 00:14:17,280
The future?

310
00:14:27,360 --> 00:14:28,270
Don't sit.

311
00:14:32,440 --> 00:14:34,030
Who knows
if there will even be a future?

312
00:14:37,910 --> 00:14:39,360
If there really is a future

313
00:14:39,630 --> 00:14:41,150
and we might get out of here,

314
00:14:42,480 --> 00:14:43,480
is there anything

315
00:14:43,600 --> 00:14:45,000
you particularly want to do?

316
00:14:46,440 --> 00:14:47,280
Yes.

317
00:14:47,630 --> 00:14:48,470
What?

318
00:14:48,870 --> 00:14:50,510
I really want to ride my bike

319
00:14:50,510 --> 00:14:53,240
and race across the vast grasslands.

320
00:14:54,360 --> 00:14:55,840
I want to see the aurora.

321
00:14:57,360 --> 00:14:58,550
I want to meet

322
00:14:58,550 --> 00:15:00,390
my idol, John Lone.

323
00:15:01,150 --> 00:15:03,870
I want to watch a real boxing match.

324
00:15:09,670 --> 00:15:11,390
You're still tied with this rope.

325
00:15:13,200 --> 00:15:14,206
Let me untie it for you.

326
00:15:16,670 --> 00:15:18,440
If I really die here today,

327
00:15:19,870 --> 00:15:21,480
this will be my only funerary item.

328
00:15:54,670 --> 00:15:56,320
This is so unfair.

329
00:15:56,910 --> 00:15:58,360
I'm almost buried here.

330
00:15:59,360 --> 00:16:00,480
You're nothing.

331
00:16:01,360 --> 00:16:03,270
There are greater things.

332
00:16:04,200 --> 00:16:06,270
There's a princess's tomb

333
00:16:06,750 --> 00:16:08,510
with a male corpse inside.

334
00:16:09,360 --> 00:16:11,670
This man slipped into the tomb passage.

335
00:16:12,080 --> 00:16:13,270
Guess what?

336
00:16:15,480 --> 00:16:17,550
He was the princess's lover.

337
00:16:18,240 --> 00:16:20,550
He came in

338
00:16:20,550 --> 00:16:23,150
- to be with the princess forever.
- A lover.

339
00:16:23,720 --> 00:16:24,630
Amazing.

340
00:16:24,790 --> 00:16:25,630
Nonsense.

341
00:16:26,240 --> 00:16:28,000
That one snuck in.

342
00:16:28,510 --> 00:16:29,360
This guy

343
00:16:30,080 --> 00:16:32,030
was openly buried here.

344
00:16:32,200 --> 00:16:33,910
If he were the princess's lover,

345
00:16:34,080 --> 00:16:37,360
would the emperor have allowed him
to be buried here?

346
00:16:39,240 --> 00:16:40,870
The emperor didn't approve of us.

347
00:16:41,360 --> 00:16:43,000
We're still here with her, aren't we?

348
00:16:45,360 --> 00:16:46,200
Take it.

349
00:17:04,270 --> 00:17:07,370
♪A tiny ark sails;
the sky opens its eyes♪

350
00:17:09,050 --> 00:17:12,730
